This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with biomedical image segmentation. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category as it discusses the use of skip connections in fully convolutional networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the development of deep learning models for image analysis. Neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) are also possible categories as they are related to the use of deep learning for image analysis.
